  "text": "It is important to make sure that the fluid will be infused at the prescribed rate. Adverse events can occur if a large continuous infusion dose is administered via accidental rapid infusion. An observational study showed that errors in infusion rates accounted for 10.9% of drug-related problems associated with intravenous medication administration. [CITATION_1] A questionnaire survey showed that the wrong infusion rate (33.3%) was the most prevalent type of medication errors of nurses in the emergency department. [CITATION_2] ",
